AB  - Wireless sensor networks are widely used as the prospect of a new type of information acquisition and processing techniques, both at home and abroad has aroused academic and industry attention. In this paper, quantum genetic algorithm is used to optimize the path in wireless sensor networks, and use energy consumption and routing node recovery time and other factors as the actual path of the constraint optimization problem, in accordance with the importance of considering the various constraints and the priority of multiple goals. Quantum Genetic Algorithm on all aspects is analyzed in detail, including the quantum encoding, fitness function design, update quantum gates, quantum and other variations. The simulation results show, quantum genetic algorithm is an effective measure of optimization of wireless sensor networks routing, and better than the correlation algorithm.
