AU  - Joshi, Sangeeta M.
AU  - Awale, R. N.
TI  - Performance evaluation of novel low leakage Double-gate FinFET device at sub-22nm with LaAlO3 high-k gate oxide and TiN metal gate using quantum modeling
LA  - eng
JF  - 2014 International Conference on Electronics and Communication Systems, Icecs 2014
PY  - 2014
SN  - 1479923206, 1479923214, 147996638X, 147996638x, 9781479923205, 9781479923212, 9781479966387
PB  - Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.
DO  - 10.1109/ECS.2014.6892692
AB  - The impact of metal gate work function on the device performance of 22 nm Double-gate FinFET with SiO2 and high-k gate oxide LaAlO3 is studied over a wide range of work functions. Matlab is used to calculate equivalent oxide thickness of high-k material LaAlO3 and simulations are carried out in PADRE device simulator. Quantum-mechanical effects such as Band to Band Tunnelling, Band Gap Narrowing, Carrier-Carrier Scattering are taken care of in the simulation by including the nonlinear drift velocity model and Lombardi's transverse field dependent mobility model. We propose a novel device with high-k LaAlO3 and the metal gate TiN. Our results show improvement in on-current, transconductance and degradation in the short channel effects DIBL and subthreshold swing. Using matlab the effect of fin width and underlap length on the fringing capacitance of DG-FinFET is also simulated. To achieve low leakage, optimizations of fin width and underlap length are done via simulations. From our results we propose that a fin width in the range of 6nm-8nm and an underlap length of 3nm are suitable for the novel DG-FinFET structure at 22nm gate length with high-k LaAlO3 and metal gate TiN.
ER  -

