AB  - The proceedings contain 18 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Artificial Intelligence and Knowledge Processing. The topics include: Deciphering Excellence in Hospitality: A Study on India's Premier Hotels Using Natural Language Processing; Decoding Student Feedback in Engineering Education: A Latent Dirichlet Allocation and PyLDAvis Approach; real Time Traffic Management by Optimizing Level of Service; FGA-Net: Feature-Gated Attention for Glioma Brain Tumor Segmentation in Volumetric MRI Images; empowering Breast Cancer Detection: A Novel Hybrid Transfer Learning Approach with Aquila Optimizer; predictive Analytics in Weather Forecasting Using Machine Learning and Deep Learning; Brain Tumor Classification from MRI Scans Using a Novel CNN Architecture and Optimization Techniques; dual Model Dynamics: Enhancing Depression Prediction Through the Integrated Use of Convolutional Neural Networks and Support Vector Machines in Data-Driven Methods; quantum Simulation of 1D and 2D Lattice-Based Magnetic Quantum Systems Using Heisenberg Model via Variational Quantum Eigensolver; topological Quantum Computing for Engineers; traffic Forecasting with Spatio-Temporal Graph Neural Networks; A Deep Learning-Based Novel RNN-BiLSTM Architecture for Efficient Threat Detection in IoT Ecosystem; cyber-Attack Detection in Healthcare Systems Based on Modified -Recurrent Neural Network Approach; A Comparative Analysis of Aggregation Methods in Federated Learning on MNIST; hybrid Feature Approach for Enhancing Zero-Shot Image Classification; abusive Comment Detection from Bengali-English Code-Mixed Social Media Texts Using Ensemble of Deep Learning.
