AB  - The proceedings contain 129 papers. The topics discussed include: consistency based attribute reduction; multiscale bilinear recurrent neutral neural network for prediction of MPEG video traffic; an optimum random forest model for prediction of genetic susceptibility to complex diseases; scaling up semi-supervised learning: an efficient and effective LLGC variant; estimation of class membership probabilities in the document classification; a clustering algorithm based on mechanics; a rough set approach to classifying web page without negative examples; evolution and maintenance of frequent pattern space when transaction are removed; reducing overfitting in predicting intrinsically unstructured proteins; temporal relations extraction in mining hepatitis data; an advanced fuzzy C-mean algorithm for regional clustering of interconnected systems; quantum-inspired immune clonal multiobjective optimization algorithm; and principal curves with feature continuity.
