PB  - Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.
DO  - 10.1109/CAC48633.2019.8996357
AB  - In order to meet the Ubiquitous Power Internet of things (UPI) which can holographic sense power data, a new wireless sensor network(WSN) clustering routing protocol which based on Smart grid is proposed to solve the problem of data loss, retransmission and invalidation in the power communication network of Smart grid. Firstly, the algorithm uses the combination of Quantum optimization algorithm and particle swarm optimization algorithm to construct a network model of dual cluster heads to improve the robustness of the system. Then the adaptive value function of main and sub-cluster heads is optimized to make them cooperate in data fusion and transmission. Finally, a high performance network transmission path selection model is established to select the optimum path and complete the inter-cluster communication. Simulations show that this algorithm can effectively balance the energy consumption of the entire network while improving the real-time performance and reducing the problem of unstable data transmission in power communication network.
