AB  - For the problem of multiple routes planning to realize the weapon cooperation in complex environment, K-means clustering is improved by an exclusion mechanism which generates the initial cluster centers. A method combining quantum-behaved particle swarm optimization (QPSO) with K-means clustering is proposed and applied to 3-D multiple routes planning of unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV). The improved algorithm solves the problem of falling in local best and improves the clustering accuracy. It classifies the particles to several subgroups. Then every subgroup is optimized by QPSO so as to generate a feasible route. Finally, multiple and dispersive routes are constituted. Simulation proves that the improved algorithm can assure the variety of subgroups and generates feasible and diverse routes.
