AB  - The proceedings contain 180 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Future Technologies. The topics include: Pre-trained CNN Based SVM Classifier for Weld Joint Type Recognition; A Two-Stage Federated Transfer Learning Framework in Medical Images Classification on Limited Data: A COVID-19 Case Study; Graph Emotion Distribution Learning Using EmotionGCN; on the Role of Depth Predictions for 3D Human Pose Estimation; AI-Based QOS/QOE Framework for Multimedia Systems; snatch Theft Detection Using Deep Learning Models; deep Learning and Few-Shot Learning in the Detection of Skin Cancer: An Overview; enhancing Artificial Intelligence Control Mechanisms: Current Practices, Real Life Applications and Future Views; Face Generation from Skull Photo Using GAN and 3D Face Models; a General Framework of Particle Swarm Optimization; how Artificial Intelligence and Videogames Drive Each Other Forward; bezier Curve-Based Shape Knowledge Acquisition and Fusion for Surrogate Model Construction; Path Planning and Landing for Unmanned Aerial Vehicles Using AI; digital Ticketing System for Public Transport in Mexico to Avoid Cases of Contagion Using Artificial Intelligence; To the Question of the Practical Implementation of “Digital Immortality” Technologies: New Approaches to the Creation of AI; collaborative Forecasting Using “Slider-Swarms” Improves Probabilistic Accuracy; learning to Solve Sequential Planning Problems Without Rewards; systemic Analysis of Democracies and Concept of Their Further Human-Technological Development; using Regression and Algorithms in Artificial Intelligence to Predict the Price of Bitcoin; exploring Deep Learning in Road Traffic Accident Recognition for Roadside Sensing Technologies; integration of Human-Driven and Autonomous Vehicle: A Cell Reservation Intersection Control Strategy; equivalence Between Classical Epidemic Model and Quantum Tight-Binding Model; effects of Various Barricades on Human Crowd Movement Flow; the Classical Logic and the Continuous Logic; editor’s Preface.
