AB  - Great honor to have your supports to 2021 2nd International Conference on Modeling, Big Data Analytics and Simulation (MBDAS2021) and participation in this academic discussion mainly direct at modelling and simulation, simulation optimization, mathematical modeling, time series analysis, complex system modeling and simulation, big data analytics and metrics, big data quality and provenance control, intelligent computing, quantum computing and related areas. Due to the severe impact of Covid-19 and the travel restrictions, most of the authors can’t attend the conference physically. The organizing committee of MBDAS2021 actively response to the call for epidemic prevention and control and adopt virtual form to conduct this academic conference. MBDAS2021 is rescheduled to be held via Tencent Meeting, November 15, 2021. The conference staff send a formal email notification to all the authors and participants before the meeting, try our best to co-ordinate the meeting and possibly make sure that all the details are in place. We set test room for our experts and authors to have a test on their video, audio and screen sharing, etc. in order to avoid the network meeting uncertainty. This virtual mainly conduct in the forms of Keynote Speech, Oral presentations, Posters, Free discussion. It is great honor to invite five senior experts at here to share their keynote speeches to us. The first expert is Prof. Hui-Ming Wee from College of Electrical Engineering & Computer Science, Chung Yuan Christian University, Taiwan. The second expert is Prof. Christophe Claramunt from Naval Academy Research Institute & Arts & Métiers Institute of Technology, France. The third expert is Prof. Cheng Siong Chin from Newcastle University in Singapore, Singapore. The fourth expert is Prof. Stefano Zedda from Department of Business and Economics, University of Cagliari, Italy. The fifth expert is Prof. T. Velmurugan from Dwaraka Doss Goverdhan Doss Vaishnav College, India. They each make keynote speech for 50 minutes. And then the authors make 10mins oral presentations separately. All of them has contribute to a huge success of MBDAS2021 online conference. List of MBDAS2021 Organization Committees, Keynote Speakers, Technical Program Committees are avilable in this pdf.
