AB  - The proceedings contain 32 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Information Security and Cryptology. The topics include: Group Key Exchange Protocols from Supersingular Isogenies; a Paid Message Forwarding Scheme Based on Social Network; WebSmell: An Efficient Malicious HTTP Traffic Detection Framework Using Data Augmentation; blockchain-Based Efficient Public Integrity Auditing for Cloud Storage Against Malicious Auditors; E-SGX: Effective Cache Side-Channel Protection for Intel SGX on Untrusted OS; public Verifiable Private Decision Tree Prediction; P2A: Privacy Preserving Anonymous Authentication Based on Blockchain and SGX; spectrum Privacy Preserving for Social Networks: A Personalized Differential Privacy Approach; LPPRS: New Location Privacy Preserving Schemes Based on Ring Signature over Mobile Social Networks; DAS-AST: Defending Against Model Stealing Attacks Based on Adaptive Softmax Transformation; On the Structure Property of PCR’s Adjacency Graph with a Prime Order and Its Application of Constructing M-Sequences; symmetric 2-Adic Complexity of Ding-Helleseth Generalized Cyclotomic Sequences of Period pq; A Distinguisher for RNGs with LFSR Post-processing; on the k-Error Linear Complexities of De Bruijn Sequences; A Lattice-Based Fully Dynamic Group Signature Scheme Without NIZK; An Efficient Blind Signature Scheme Based on SM2 Signature Algorithm; a New Efficient Quantum Digital Signature Scheme for Multi-bit Messages; an Improvement of Multi-exponentiation with Encrypted Bases Argument: Smaller and Faster; number Theoretic Transform: Generalization, Optimization, Concrete Analysis and Applications; On Galois NFSRs Equivalent to Fibonacci Ones; Bidirectional RNN-Based Few-Shot Training for Detecting Multi-stage Attack; Bagua: A NFSR-Based Stream Cipher Constructed Following Confusion and Diffusion Principles; provable Related-Key Security of Contracting Feistel Networks.
